<author><name><![CDATA[tim miltz]]></name></author>
<updated>2016-08-02T17:32:07-07:00</updated>
<published>2016-08-02T17:32:07-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6436&amp;p=27968#p27968</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6436&amp;p=27968#p27968"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Windows 10 post Anniversary update - won't boot]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6436&amp;p=27968#p27968"><![CDATA[
I wasn't happy to see my machine auto rebooted - losing my work while I slept<br /><br />But I realized this was the Windows 10 Anniversary update.<br /><br />So it finally comes back, and I ask myself ? Where is my ClassicShell?<br /><br />So I remember a notification yesterday a new CS is available.<br /><br />I go to install it, nothing but warnings this may damage your PC, I over ride it and it just flashes a window and closes.<br /><br />So I head to the forums here, and first thing I see is - remove the old classic shell before upgrading.<br /><br />As SOON as I removed the old classic shell, N360.exe blew a gasket - machine was locked.<br /><br />I went to reboot? and now all I have is a black screen.<br /><br />get this - bottom left, NOT top left,  I have a 'spade' symbol with a fast blinking cursor to the right of it.<br /><br />I've never seen that before - but it's not a prompt, you can't type.<br /><br />All I can do is CTRL-ALT-DELETE - pressing F8 for a 'safe mode' does not work.<br /><br />I dare say-  Somewhere between this Anniversary update and the uninstall of my Classic Shell?<br /><br />I'm looking at a complete rebuild - everything lost.<br /><br />Very sad day here indeed.<br /><br />Anyone else having issues with classic shell and Anniversary?<br /><br />I can't believe MS EVER took away that nice standard Start Menu.<br /> <br />TOTAL BONUS - I only ever 'bought' Windows 8.1,  and although I did upgrade using the free upgrade?<br /><br />I am anticipating when I re-install 8.1, I won't get that 10 upgrade since it ended 3 days ago.<br /><br />Thoughts anyone?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=14485">tim miltz</a> — Tue Aug 02, 2016 5:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
